column1: #Text=About Who You Are and Be Confident
#Text=In the World that we live in today , it is hard for people to find and be okay with themselves .
#Text=This can be especially hard if you are a teenager or if you are more sensitive than most people .
#Text=The things that you were told as a child and the beliefs that you have placed upon yourself because of this might have a dramatic effect on the reason why finding yourself seems so difficult .
#Text=Recognize the negative messages you 've been told .
#Text=Or the beliefs you have about yourself and when you tell yourself these messages the most .
#Text=When you feel insecure about the way you look ?

#Text=This is important to know because once you know where your irrational beliefs are coming from it will be easier for you to tackle them and get on track to finding yourself and build confidence .
#Text=Once you have recognized the messages you 've been believing or telling yourself , its then that you can change them .
#Text=It 's okay if you ca n't get to the root of it right away .

#Text=Spend some time , read stories of others with the same struggles as you , listen to songs a lot of times songs will analyze struggles and might even offer advice , Try to get a therapist/counselor but pay attention to whether they understand you or not .
#Text=If you catch yourself saying " I 'm so stupid " or " I 'm a failure " all the time .
#Text=You do n't have to go from saying I 'm so stupid to I 'm so smart .
#Text=Stay neutral at first then when you 're ready , go for the positive .
#Text=Try saying positive statements to yourself , like , " I am a positive force in the world !
